    "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::drift_baseline_uses_current_sample::048c00dc": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::drift_baseline_uses_current_sample::048c00dc",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "The drift detector mutates its rolling window before evaluating drift, which dilutes every spike against itself.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "low_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "src/shared/drift.ts",
          "src/shared/drift.test.ts",
          "src/server/index.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "In `src/shared/drift.ts`, `check()` pushes `value` into `window.values` and updates `window.sum` before computing `baseline` and `deviationPct`, so the candidate event is included in the baseline it is being judged against.",
          "`src/shared/drift.test.ts` asserts severities produced by that diluted baseline instead of asserting against the prior window, so the current tests reinforce the misleading threshold behavior that `src/server/index.ts` relies on for live alerts."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Compute drift against the pre-existing window, then append the new sample after classification. Update the tests to build a baseline window first and assert severities against the untouched baseline so threshold meanings remain stable.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-02T01:44:24+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-02T01:44:24+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
