    "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::transport_to_storage_handoff_has_no_policy_seam::5550843f": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::mid_level_elegance::transport_to_storage_handoff_has_no_policy_seam::5550843f",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Request handlers pass anonymous transport payloads straight into storage and runtime state with no normalization seam.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "mid_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "src/server/index.ts",
          "src/db/queries.ts",
          "src/shared/events.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Handlers in `src/server/index.ts` cast `req.body` and `req.query` directly (`as TelemetryEvent`, `as RagProviderConfig`, `as any`) and then call `ingestAndBroadcast()`, `ragProviders.set()`, or store getters without an intermediate boundary object.",
          "`ingestAndBroadcast()` combines redaction, persistence, provider bookkeeping, drift generation, and dashboard broadcast, so the only seam between external callers and internal state is a single untyped event object.",
          "`src/db/queries.ts` depends on event-type-specific JSON fields already being trustworthy, which means validation, authorization, and shape translation were never given a dedicated integration layer."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Refactor the server into route groups with explicit ingress services: one for dashboard reads, one for collector/event writes, and one for admin/provider operations. Each ingress service should authenticate the caller, validate a route-specific DTO, translate it into an internal command/event, and only then call storage/broadcast code.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-02T01:44:24+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-02T01:44:24+00:00",
