    "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::silent_empty_fallbacks_hide_request_failures::33507443": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::silent_empty_fallbacks_hide_request_failures::33507443",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Dashboard fetch helpers collapse transport errors into empty data, so callers cannot distinguish 'no telemetry yet' from 'API failed'.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "src/dashboard/hooks/useTelemetry.ts",
          "src/server/index.ts",
          "src/dashboard/visualizations/McpStatsPanel.tsx",
          "src/dashboard/visualizations/RagStatsPanel.tsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "In `useTelemetry.ts`, methods such as `fetchSessionEvents`, `fetchToolStats`, `fetchMcpStats`, `fetchRagStats`, `fetchDriftEvents`, and many others `catch` and return `[]`; `fetchLatestBreakdown` returns `{ segments: [] }` on failure.",
          "The corresponding routes in `src/server/index.ts` legitimately return empty arrays or empty objects for valid states, so the fallback values are indistinguishable from a healthy-but-empty response.",
          "Panels like `McpStatsPanel` and `RagStatsPanel` render 'No ... recorded' for empty arrays, which means backend outages are rendered as lack of activity instead of an error state."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Change the hook helpers to return an explicit result shape such as `{ ok: true, data } | { ok: false, error }`, or at minimum surface a per-request error flag so empty telemetry and failed requests remain distinguishable.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
