        "evidence": [
          "`traceMcp()` and `traceRetrieval()` both catch failures, emit error telemetry, and rethrow.",
          "`traceEmbedding()` and `traceIndex()` directly await `fn()` and emit only on success, so failed embedding/index operations disappear from telemetry entirely.",
          "`createRagTracer()` in `src/sdk/rag.ts` exposes `traceRetrieval`, `traceEmbedding`, and `traceIndex` as same-level API methods, but they do not share a consistent contract for emitted events or failure observability."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Normalize all trace helpers to the same contract: emit start/end or success/error telemetry for every traced operation, and document whether automatic latency events are included. If one operation type intentionally differs, expose it under a distinct API name.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
