    "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::session_cost_double_count::49cd6e16": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::session_cost_double_count::49cd6e16",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Collector and store both count the same spend twice in session totals",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "src/collector/index.ts",
          "src/db/queries.ts",
          "src/dashboard/pages/DashboardPage.tsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "The collector sends a `token_usage` event carrying `u.cost` and then sends a separate `cost` event for the same assistant turn in [src/collector/index.ts](/Users/donovanadams/Desktop/hydrotik/packages/hy-ai-rum/src/collector/index.ts).",
          "`TelemetryStore.ingestEvent()` adds `e.cost.total` to `sessions.total_cost` for `token_usage` and adds `e.totalCost` again for `cost` in [src/db/queries.ts](/Users/donovanadams/Desktop/hydrotik/packages/hy-ai-rum/src/db/queries.ts).",
          "`DashboardPage` renders `activeSession.totalCost` as the KPI, so the double-counted storage value is shown directly in the UI in [src/dashboard/pages/DashboardPage.tsx](/Users/donovanadams/Desktop/hydrotik/packages/hy-ai-rum/src/dashboard/pages/DashboardPage.tsx)."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Choose one canonical accounting path. Either keep `token_usage.cost` purely informational and stop mutating `sessions.total_cost` from that event, or stop emitting a separate `cost` event from the collector when token usage already carries priced totals. Then backfill or invalidate old session totals so historical dashboards are not permanently inflated.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-02T01:44:24+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-02T01:44:24+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "typescript",
      "suppressed": false,
