        "related_files": [
          "src/dashboard/hooks/useTelemetry.ts",
          "src/dashboard/pages/DashboardPage.tsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`useTelemetry()` exports websocket state plus more than a dozen endpoint-specific callbacks in [src/dashboard/hooks/useTelemetry.ts](/Users/donovanadams/Desktop/hydrotik/packages/hy-ai-rum/src/dashboard/hooks/useTelemetry.ts), but it does not assemble session-scoped dashboard data.",
          "`DashboardPage` still owns separate state for events, tool calls, context snapshots, breakdown, MCP, RAG, latency, cost, evals, prompts, drift, and timeseries in [src/dashboard/pages/DashboardPage.tsx](/Users/donovanadams/Desktop/hydrotik/packages/hy-ai-rum/src/dashboard/pages/DashboardPage.tsx).",
          "The hook/page split therefore introduces indirection while preserving the full fetch choreography, refresh policy, and data-shape patching in the consumer."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Refactor the dashboard data layer around one session-scoped hook such as `useSessionDashboard(sessionId)` that owns resource loading, incremental refresh, and normalized return types. Keep the websocket connection in `useTelemetry()`, but move panel-level resource orchestration behind typed selectors so `DashboardPage` becomes composition instead of transport glue.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
