    "review::.::holistic::authorization_consistency::network_exposed_mutation_endpoints_have_no_gate::a61b1583": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::authorization_consistency::network_exposed_mutation_endpoints_have_no_gate::a61b1583",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "The server exposes write endpoints to any reachable origin without authentication",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "authorization_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "src/server/index.ts",
          "src/server/cli.ts",
          "src/server/start.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "The CLI binds to `0.0.0.0` by default in [src/server/cli.ts](/Users/donovanadams/Desktop/hydrotik/packages/hy-ai-rum/src/server/cli.ts), and the alternate launcher does the same in [src/server/start.ts](/Users/donovanadams/Desktop/hydrotik/packages/hy-ai-rum/src/server/start.ts).",
          "The server enables `cors({ origin: true })` and accepts unauthenticated writes on `/api/ingest`, `/api/ingest/batch`, `/api/rag/*`, and `/api/providers/rag` in [src/server/index.ts](/Users/donovanadams/Desktop/hydrotik/packages/hy-ai-rum/src/server/index.ts).",
          "Because there is no shared auth or shared-origin check, any browser origin or host on the reachable network can inject telemetry, create fake providers, or poison the local dashboard dataset."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Add a single ingress policy for all mutating routes: require a bearer token or local-only bind by default, restrict CORS to an explicit allowlist, and apply the same guard to websocket collector ingress plus every POST route. If this server is intentionally single-user, invert the defaults so `127.0.0.1` is the default host and remote exposure requires an explicit flag.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
